Augmentative communication boards are aids for people who are not verbal, i.e. people who do not have oral language.
This condition can occur from birth, for example in the case of children with severe autism spectrum disorders, or for example in children with cerebral palsy.
Also this condition can occur when you are already an adult, because you have a stroke or because you have an accident, or because you suffer a neurodegenerative disease, such as Parkinson’s.
These boards that we use for the project are composed of pictograms and core vocabulary.
